rComments: Super nice and accommodating professor. He was very kind with grading in the first summer semester of the pandemic (I ended this class with approx 107%) but I don't think that's his status quo. He is a very gentle, thorough guide through the course material and I think his style is very effective for an introduction.

Professor Lethbridge is a perfect example of how a professor should guide a student on a course. He is an excellent mentor who explains the classes with detailed examples and connects dots with real-life scenarios. Always available, even on weekends, to respond to student's queries. Very helpful. I have so much respect for this professor.

Professor Lethbridge is a prime example of how professors should be handling their courses given the current pandemic. Timothy was very accomodating in terms of marking, which alleviated tons of stress amongst students. I have so much respect for this professor. You can tell he genuinely cares about his students, unlike other profs.

Dr. Lethbridge cares for his students a lot. Because of the pandemic, he modified the class to make it less stressful and giving us a chance to learn. He also gave excellent feedback on quizzes and gave lots of bonus marks on assignments. He even interviewed certain people who worked in a company to give students an idea of what's to come.

Professor Lethbridge cares about his students and it really shows. Due to the pandemic, he was a lot more lenient with his marking and he gave out a LOT of bonuses to let students boost their mark. His assignments are long and tedious, but they help you learn. He is accessible outside of class and gives pretty good feedback.
Lethbridge is the GOAT professor, great teaching, great slides, very accommodating, very nice. You're doing a disservice to yourself if you don't take a course with him.

This prof is solid. Very organized course, clear in his expectations, everything in the course runs smoothly and no headaches for the students. Always responds promptly to emails and provides any help needed. Also his lectures are fantastic! Really adds to the lecture slides (which are also well organized and clear). Absolutely take his class.
He is a great guy.

He should be teaching the classes in software engineering. You need to get used to him and his way of teaching. Once you do, other teachers will have nothing on him.  Already miss having him as a teacher. Class is not a joke... make sure to do your work.

Awesome course and awesome teacher. Content is very useful and so interesting to learn. Lecturer is enthusiastic and knows what he is talking about. He's happy to help and wants students to succeed. TopHat questions are good for testing knowledge too.

You will hate him at first but he will grow on you.  He is seems more strict in class than he actually is. Midterm and final seem very hard but he grade pretty easily.  Midterm and final are open book Can't avoid Umple The non programming assignments are subjective so argue as much as you can with the ta's. Assignments worth 30%.(easy grades)

Lethbridge is okay at what he does. He bases the class on his own book, so it's generally very easy to get an A+, much less pass. He is rather annoying, but at least he's not boring. He goes on interesting rants and when he's wrong about something his reactions are downright hilarious; he gets really flustered. Easy course -- take it for that.

Deviates from the useful material in order to shamelessly promote his research project UMPLE. Several assignments and labs were actually dedicated to the use of this broken and slow software. This is ironic considering this course is meant to teach proper software engineering. Most assignments are vague and haphazard. He also patronizes  students.

Love Timothy Lethbridge. A very involved, passionate professor who loves engineering and computer science. Among the best profs at Uottawa. Just wish this was a more interesting course. I guess it's a good way to raise your GPA because both midterm and final are multiple choice/open book, and TAs are really easy on you on assignments/essays.
Worst prof! very annoying with his emails (like an average of 3 per day). he love who he is (he made a wikipedia page of him) Very annoying in front of the class.
Very helpful prof and always fast at replying to emails.
ineffective, inefficient, instruction is sub par and ability to admister a course is even worse. just bad at his job. would avoid at all costs in the future.
Great Prof loool

Textbook is useless. Open note exams, easy to do well on those. Interesting guest speakers. Presenting in front of the whole class was challenging but the marking of them seemed relaxed/fair. A few essays to write though! Overall a boring class in which not that much is learned for which there is not much of an excuse not to get an A+.
He seems like a good prof at first but, then it gets really annoying having to listen to him. His tests are really hard. And he's a hard marker.

This guy has been teaching this course since the stone age!!! make sure u go to his classes don't skip the exams are literally questions from things he actually said in his lectures!!! SERIOUSLY DONT SKIP!!! over all he is ok not my favorite for sure
extremely knowledgeable in his field and that makes him a good professor..his exams aren't difficult if you know what your dealing with

Really professional and easy to understand.  Explains well, and will answers any questions you have in class. He wrote the textbook used in the course; this is a god thing because he knows how to communicate the info effectively.  Midterms are open-book.
Good professor

Very professional and charismatic. He enjoys teaching the material which makes it more enjoyable to learn. Likes to make references to his own published works even when unneccessary, but that's more of a quirk than a flaw. Course material is easy and well-structured, even easier if you have already taken SEG3300.

He's definitly a professional in His field. Always Busy in his office, so you gotta be quick with your questions. He's kind. But makes alot of comments on how Indians are taking over the market. Well Globalisation shouldn't suit only North America??

Definitely a PROFESSIONAL and EXPERT in his domain. Clear, logically structured notes,interesting and challenging assignments. Motivates whole class throughout the course. However, demands a lot, so if you want a good mark, u gotta work for it. Strongly recommended.
WOW ... that's all i could say ... one of the best profs ever ... especially when you have zhao in SEG2101 , you'll know how wonderful lethbridge was
Very good prof. clear notes, clear lectures. Assists students often. Definitely recommended.
He is an ok prof.  Average.  He uses his own book to teach and taped himself in the class.  Not a bad prof.

Awesome course due to his awesome teaching. He gets so into teaching he sweats a lot. Pleasant semi-British accent. Very descriptive and concise teaching. He wrote the book for this course, which is also awesome. Why can't SEG2101 be anything like this&#6
good prof. really into teaching. puts in effort to help.
Good prof, know material, is clear, helps students, what more can you ask for&#6
